@ChampagnePablo this tweet was less of buying longterm but focusing on things like creating connections or going out and building something.
Also obviously if you can secure money do it, I love flipping the market as much as anyone else. But that shouldn't be the only thing you are focusing on.

This tweet doesn't mean holding all your nfts longterm will pay off either. There will be winners and losers but something you cant really regret is the people you met or companies you tried to create.
@itstylersays Trusting myself more than ever & working on bringing as much quality as I can to this community. Memes are fun & all but there is a ton happening behind that as well.

Quick money can be made whenever in life but the connections you can create & the products you can build in Web3 are at an all time high right now.

Focus on the longterm.
You can like something or believe in it longterm but realize the market overpriced it at the moment. This has nothing to do with the product or team but just the hype nature of this market.

btw this tweet is purely speculating the market, not the product or team. I like invisible friends but the market over pumped it. Like I said before, sometimes you can like something but realize its over priced at the moment.

@onlitario @Loopifyyy @InvsbleFriends I like invisible friends a lot, but yes at that price the market over pumped it (not the projects fault). I also never made fun of the art, the meme I shared was funny and doesn't hate on the art.

As often as we call out bad actors in this space, it's very important to realize how many good builders there are.

Creating a project is very tough, and creating a successful one is even harder. With floor prices always moving & discord 24/7 active it's a never ending job.
